description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title and Grade:&lt;/strong&gt; Band 6 CAMHS Practitioner &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location/Trust:&lt;/strong&gt; Rotherham, Doncaster, and South Humber NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department Covered:&lt;/strong&gt; St Nicholas House, Scunthorpe - CAMHS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Rates:  &lt;/strong&gt;Days: £19.38 Nights/Saturdays: £25.19 Sundays/Bank Holiday: £31.00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is good to talk…let’s talk about bringing your CAMHS skills to the staff bank Rotherham, Doncaster, and South Humber NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Social Worker or Registered Mental Health Nurse who would like to be part of a multi-disciplinary specialist CAMHS team, developing and delivering a clinical service to children and young people under the age of 18 years?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you answered yes, then we would like to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based at St Nicholas House, Scunthorpe, North Lincolnshire you will be an independent practitioner, with accountability and responsibility for managing a clinical caseload within Specialist CAMHS. You will provide patient-centred assessment, care planning, implementation and evaluation with children, young people (up to 18 years), parents and families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a placement opportunity (initially 3 months) available for a Band 6 CAMHS Practitioner post at Rotherham, Doncaster, and South Humber NHS Foundation Trust, specifically providing the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To assess and treat children and adolescents who have a range of mental health, behavioural and psychological needs.  Also, to support supervise and consult to other CAMHS Team members engaged in the assessment process&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To develop joint collaborative approaches with other agencies involved in a patient’s care, i.e. Social Services, Department of Education, and the Voluntary Services.  To develop a flexible range of care plans and interventions to meet needs of patients, their carer’s and referrers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Identify the communication needs of children, young people and families taking into account culture, ethnicity and special needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensure that agreed policies and procedures are implemented consistently with particular emphasis on achieving compliance with Improving Working Lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participate in delegated projects within CAMHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participate weekly in urgent rota&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work in sites, other than designated base i.e. on a ward, family centres or in patients’ homes/child care units.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employing around 4,750 members of staff, who deliver services from more than 130 locations, GMMH people are passionate, patient focused, positive individuals, who are committed to working together to help people live well, striving to give their people a great work experience where they feel supported and valued.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills/Responsibilities:&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this post, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appropriate professional qualification e.g. RMN Social Worker or Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Registered with the appropriate professional body.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Extensive mental health experience post qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appropriate student teaching and assessing in clinical practice accreditation or a willingness to complete the appropriate course.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge and experience of clinical and management supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work commitment NHS Professionals (NHSP) can offer you some fantastic benefits: –&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Pay Rates &lt;/strong&gt;- work this week, get paid next week!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First choice of placements at over 50 NHS Trusts in England&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dedicated consultants&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible working options&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Free DBS and free training&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build holiday allowance &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support when you need it – 24/7 365 days – &lt;/strong&gt;Call us anytime on 03330 144 370&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder pension scheme&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are NHS Professionals?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Professionals (NHSP), owned by the Department of Health and Social Care (DHSC), works in partnership with hospital trusts to provide a bank of highly skilled temporary workers who want to work flexibly within the NHS. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working through the NHSP bank means Trusts don’t have to rely on expensive agencies. Right now, we have over 130,000 members registered on our bank from various roles, grades and specialities, saving the NHS over &lt;strong&gt;£70 million&lt;/strong&gt; each year. This money is then reinvested back into the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information on the roles or details on how to join NHS Professionals, simply get in touch with Ellie Watson on 03330144370 or ellie.watson@nhsprofessionals.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to hearing from you soon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disclaimer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note, you will be contacted by email throughout the recruitment process, so please check your emails, including your junk/spam regularly. We regret we cannot contact everyone who is not selected for an interview, therefore if you do not hear from us within 21 days after submitting your application, please assume you have not been successful on this occasion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
